WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:30.200 --> 00:00:41.330
Cut the 2 cucumbers into sticks.

00:00:41.800 --> 00:00:51.130
Cut the 1 young yellowtail fillet into thin slices.

00:00:51.600 --> 00:01:01.000
Cut the 1 lean tuna fillet into rectangles.

00:01:01.470 --> 00:01:18.200
Cut the 1 squid fillet into thin strips.

00:01:18.670 --> 00:01:31.730
Make 1 or 2 scores on the mackerel skin's surface, for every slice about to be cut.
(This fish-cutting technique is "kirikake-zukuri", often use "sashimi".)

00:01:32.200 --> 00:01:38.930
"kirikake-zukuri"
Make 1 or 2 scores the skin, for every slice about to be cut.

00:01:39.400 --> 00:01:46.200
This technique makes both the skin and trunk easier to eat, and easier for the soy sauce to soak into the fish.

00:01:51.670 --> 00:02:15.000
Arrange the ingredients on a large plate.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:37.870
For garnish, with shiso leaves (green perilla).
Arrange on the plate in a well-balanced.
When beautifully arranged, your dishes look even more delicious.

00:02:38.470 --> 00:02:52.000
Arrange the 1 pack salmon roe in a small bowl.

00:02:52.600 --> 00:03:02.530
Arrange the marinated mackerel on another plate with shiso leaves.

00:03:08.070 --> 00:03:23.200
Put the 6 tbsp sugar (90ml), 2 tsp salt (10ml), and 7 tbsp vinegar (105ml) into a small pot.
And stir well until dissolve. If it is difficult to dissolve, heat the pot slightly.
This liquid is a "sushi vinegar".

00:03:23.670 --> 00:03:38.800
Put the 5 cups cooked rice (as hot as possible) in the "Handai" (or a large bowl),
and pour the "sushi vinegar" over the rice evenly. Then mix with cutting motion.
("Handai" is a rice tub, used to make sushi rice.)

00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:46.870
When mixing is completed, cool the rice with a hand-fan.
Allow it to cool at body temperature.

00:03:47.270 --> 00:03:53.270
Cut the toasted "nori" seaweed into easy-to-roll sheets, and serve. It's done.

